@database ReadMe.guide

@width 77

@Node Main "ReadMe"

                          January 1, 1994

This unregistered MachV is release 5.0 version 37.5. It is the same as 
the registered version except this version has a "welcome" window and 
has a limit of 25 macros. It has been localized for deutsch and francais. 
2.04 or later required.

   @{" Important       " Link Important}
   @{" Highlights      " Link Highlights}
   @{" Installation    " Link Installation}
   @{" Files On Disk   " Link FilesOnDisk}
   @{" Acknowledgments " Link Acknowledgments}
   @{" UpdateInfo      " Link UpdateInfo}

@EndNode

@Node Important "Important"

---------->>   IMPORTANT INFORMATION REGARDING VERSION 5.0   <<----------

MachV will read your existing MachIV.prefs file from the directory
ENVARC:MachIV. However, it will read ENVARC:MachV/MachV.prefs if that
exists. There are some minor changes that you may need to make in your
macros. They are described in the file Update50.doc.

MachV requires the library mach.library in your libs: directory.

ARexx port renamed to MACHV_REXX. See Fixes.doc.
                           
@EndNode

@Node Highlights "Highlights"

The mach.library gives programmers access to most of MachV. SetMachV is
written using this library and the global data area.

Environment variables are completely supported.

The clock is now an "AppWindow". You can drop icons into it which will
set the environment variable "MachVar" which may then be used in macros.

The clock can be set to pick which screens it can go to. ~(Final Copy#?)

Most mouse features like SunMouse and ClickToFront will have the ability
to pick and choose which windows they operate on by using wildcards.

ARexx commands can be sent directly to ARexx ports.

Function name completion is now provided. When entering a function in the
macro string gadget, pressing <Alt-Tab> will complete the entry for you.
"Msc_Bl" will expand to "Msc_Blank_Screen".
@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

                              INSTALLATION

The script "Install" will copy the needed files to your harddrive. If you
wish to do it manually, this is the minimum needed:

  MachV          to the WBStartup drawer.
  SetMachV       to the sys:utilities or c: drawer.
  mach.library   to libs:.

You should create the directory ENVARC:MachV for your preference file.
See MachV.guide for more details.

@EndNode

@Node FilesOnDisk "About the files on this disk"

The drawer SamplePrefs contains three examples of using gadgets in the
clock. The icons in this drawer are sample icons used as gadgets by
the preference files Sample.prefs, Dock.prefs, and ProPage.prefs.
The ProPage preference is an example of multiple configurations. The 
macros specific to ProPage are in the 2nd configuration.

Due to space limitations on this disk, some files have been powerpacked.
The program ppmore can be used to read these files. The program
"decrunch" can be used to decrunch them. From the shell type:

     decrunch crunched_filename decrunched_filename

Programming documentation has been compressed using lha.

If you want the catalogs translated into another language, let us know.

Note:

  Translations of the documentation are no longer included on the disk.
They are available if desired.


@EndNode

